# DeepPPT — Cline Rules

## Project

DeepPPT: AI-driven PPT generation system. Source → Strategist → Image_Generator → Executor → PPTX.

## Authority

Read `skills/ppt-master/SKILL.md` for the full workflow before any PPT task.
Shared rules live in `docs/ai-rules-shared.md`; routing details live in `docs/routing.md`.

## Rules

1. Steps are serial. ⛔ BLOCKING steps require user confirmation.
2. SVG pages are hand-written, one at a time. No batch script generation.
3. Re-read `spec_lock.md` before each SVG page for colors/fonts/icons/images.
4. Never read/open image files. Use `analyze_images.py` output.
5. Match user's language. Design spec in English template structure.

## Key Scripts

- `project_manager.py init <name> --format ppt169` — Create project
- `dashboard/server.py <path> --daemon --no-browser` — Start/reuse read-only Dashboard after Step 2 (default port 8765; log `<path>/dashboard/dashboard.log`; failure non-fatal)
- `confirm_ui/server.py <path> --daemon --wait` — Eight Confirmations
- `image_gen.py --manifest <path>/images/image_prompts.json` — AI images
- `svg_quality_checker.py <path>` — Quality check
- `svg_to_pptx.py <path>` — Export PPTX

## Deep Research

Topic only (no source)? → `skills/ppt-master/workflows/deep-research.md` first. Do not replace it with ordinary WebSearch.

## Routing Guardrails

- Existing PPTX: preserve page count/order/wording and beautify only → `beautify-pptx`; reuse original deck design with new content → `template-fill-pptx`; restructure story or change page count/order → main pipeline + `ppt_to_md`; harvest reusable template → `create-template`.
- Dashboard is observability only; it does not replace Confirm UI, Live Preview, quality gates, post-processing, or export.
- Animation: page transitions are default; per-element animations are off unless requested. Object-level animation tuning → `customize-animations`.
- Live preview starts automatically in Step 6; apply submitted annotations only after Step 7 through `live-preview`.
- Visual review: follow current `SKILL.md`; currently `visual-review` is recommended by default after quality gates and skipped only by explicit opt-out.

## Config

`.env.example` → `.env`. Set IMAGE_BACKEND + API key.
